105 /**********************************************/
106 /* global implementation-intrinsic constants: */

109#define BIT_VECTOR_HIDDEN_WORDS 3
110
111 /*****************************************************************/
112 /* global machine-dependent constants (set by "BitVector_Boot"): */
113 /*****************************************************************/
114
115static N_word BITS; /* = # of bits in machine word (must be power of 2) */
116static N_word MODMASK; /* = BITS - 1 (mask for calculating modulo BITS) */
117static N_word LOGBITS; /* = ld(BITS) (logarithmus dualis) */
118static N_word FACTOR; /* = ld(BITS / 8) (ld of # of bytes) */
119
120static N_word LSB = 1; /* = mask for least significant bit */
121static N_word MSB; /* = mask for most significant bit */
122
123static N_word LONGBITS; /* = # of bits in unsigned long */
124
125static N_word LOG10; /* = logarithm to base 10 of BITS - 1 */
126static N_word EXP10; /* = largest possible power of 10 in signed int */
127
128 /********************************************************************/
129 /* global bit mask table for fast access (set by "BitVector_Boot"): */
130 /********************************************************************/
131
132static wordptr BITMASKTAB;
133
134 /*****************************/
135 /* global macro definitions: */
136 /*****************************/
137
138#define BIT_VECTOR_ZERO_WORDS(target,count) \
139 while (count-- > 0) *target++ = 0;
140
141#define BIT_VECTOR_FILL_WORDS(target,fill,count) \
142 while (count-- > 0) *target++ = fill;
143
144#define BIT_VECTOR_FLIP_WORDS(target,flip,count) \
145 while (count-- > 0) *target++ ^= flip;
146
147#define BIT_VECTOR_COPY_WORDS(target,source,count) \
148 while (count-- > 0) *target++ = *source++;
149
150#define BIT_VECTOR_BACK_WORDS(target,source,count) \
151 { target += count; source += count; while (count-- > 0) *--target = *--source; }
152
153#define BIT_VECTOR_CLR_BIT(address,index) \
154 *(address+(index>>LOGBITS)) &= NOT BITMASKTAB[index AND MODMASK];
155
156#define BIT_VECTOR_SET_BIT(address,index) \
157 *(address+(index>>LOGBITS)) |= BITMASKTAB[index AND MODMASK];
158
159#define BIT_VECTOR_TST_BIT(address,index) \
160 ((*(address+(index>>LOGBITS)) AND BITMASKTAB[index AND MODMASK]) != 0)
161
162#define BIT_VECTOR_FLP_BIT(address,index,mask) \
163 (mask = BITMASKTAB[index AND MODMASK]), \
164 (((*(addr+(index>>LOGBITS)) ^= mask) AND mask) != 0)
165
166#define BIT_VECTOR_DIGITIZE(type,value,digit) \
167 value = (type) ((digit = value) / 10); \
168 digit -= value * 10; \
169 digit += (type) '0';
170

172 /* private low-level functions (potentially dangerous!): */
173 /*********************************************************/

175static N_word power10(N_word x)
176{
177 N_word y = 1;
178
179 while (x-- > 0) y *= 10;
180 return(y);
181}
182
183static void BIT_VECTOR_zro_words(wordptr addr, N_word count)
184{
185 BIT_VECTOR_ZERO_WORDS(addr,count)
186}
187
188static void BIT_VECTOR_cpy_words(wordptr target, wordptr source, N_word count)
189{
190 BIT_VECTOR_COPY_WORDS(target,source,count)
191}
192
193static void BIT_VECTOR_mov_words(wordptr target, wordptr source, N_word count)
194{
195 if (target != source)
196 {
197 if (target < source) BIT_VECTOR_COPY_WORDS(target,source,count)
198 else BIT_VECTOR_BACK_WORDS(target,source,count)
199 }
200}
201
202static void BIT_VECTOR_ins_words(wordptr addr, N_word total, N_word count,
203 boolean clear)
204{
205 N_word length;
206
207 if ((total > 0) and (count > 0))
208 {
209 if (count > total) count = total;
210 length = total - count;
211 if (length > 0) BIT_VECTOR_mov_words(addr+count,addr,length);
212 if (clear) BIT_VECTOR_zro_words(addr,count);
213 }
214}
215
216static void BIT_VECTOR_del_words(wordptr addr, N_word total, N_word count,
217 boolean clear)
218{
219 N_word length;
220
221 if ((total > 0) and (count > 0))
222 {
223 if (count > total) count = total;
224 length = total - count;
225 if (length > 0) BIT_VECTOR_mov_words(addr,addr+count,length);
226 if (clear) BIT_VECTOR_zro_words(addr+length,count);
227 }
228}

230static void BIT_VECTOR_reverse(charptr string, N_word length)
231{
232 charptr last;
233 N_char temp;
234
235 if (length > 1)
236 {
237 last = string + length - 1;
238 while (string < last)
239 {
240 temp = *string;
241 *string = *last;
242 *last = temp;
243 string++;
244 last--;
245 }
246 }
247}
248
249static N_word BIT_VECTOR_int2str(charptr string, N_word value)
250{
251 N_word length;
252 N_word digit;
253 charptr work;
254
255 work = string;
256 if (value > 0)
257 {
258 length = 0;
259 while (value > 0)
260 {
261 BIT_VECTOR_DIGITIZE(N_word,value,digit)
262 *work++ = (N_char) digit;
263 length++;
264 }
265 BIT_VECTOR_reverse(string,length);
266 }
267 else
268 {
269 length = 1;
270 *work++ = (N_char) '0';
271 }
272 return(length);
273}
274
275static N_word BIT_VECTOR_str2int(charptr string, N_word *value)
276{
277 N_word length;
278 N_word digit;
279
280 *value = 0;
281 length = 0;
282 digit = (N_word) *string++;
283 /* separate because isdigit() is likely a macro! */
284 while (isdigit((int)digit) != 0)
285 {
286 length++;
287 digit -= (N_word) '0';
288 if (*value) *value *= 10;
289 *value += digit;
290 digit = (N_word) *string++;
291 }
292 return(length);
293}

299const char * BitVector_Error(ErrCode error)
300{
301 switch (error)
302 {
303 case ErrCode_Ok: return( NULL ); break;
304 case ErrCode_Type: return( ERRCODE_TYPE ); break;
305 case ErrCode_Bits: return( ERRCODE_BITS ); break;
306 case ErrCode_Word: return( ERRCODE_WORD ); break;
307 case ErrCode_Long: return( ERRCODE_LONG ); break;
308 case ErrCode_Powr: return( ERRCODE_POWR ); break;
309 case ErrCode_Loga: return( ERRCODE_LOGA ); break;
310 case ErrCode_Null: return( ERRCODE_NULL ); break;
311 case ErrCode_Indx: return( ERRCODE_INDX ); break;
312 case ErrCode_Ordr: return( ERRCODE_ORDR ); break;
313 case ErrCode_Size: return( ERRCODE_SIZE ); break;
314 case ErrCode_Pars: return( ERRCODE_PARS ); break;
315 case ErrCode_Ovfl: return( ERRCODE_OVFL ); break;
316 case ErrCode_Same: return( ERRCODE_SAME ); break;
317 case ErrCode_Expo: return( ERRCODE_EXPO ); break;
318 case ErrCode_Zero: return( ERRCODE_ZERO ); break;
319 default: return( ERRCODE_OOPS ); break;
320 }
321}

323 /*****************************************/
324 /* automatic self-configuration routine: */
325 /*****************************************/
326
327 /*******************************************************/
328 /* */
329 /* MUST be called once prior to any other function */
330 /* to initialize the machine dependent constants */
331 /* of this package! (But call only ONCE, or you */
332 /* will suffer memory leaks!) */
333 /* */
334 /*******************************************************/
335
336ErrCode BitVector_Boot(void)
337{
338 N_long longsample = 1L;
339 N_word sample = LSB;
340 N_word lsb;
341
342 if (sizeof(N_word) > sizeof(size_t)) return(ErrCode_Type);
343
344 BITS = 1;
345 while (sample <<= 1) BITS++; /* determine # of bits in a machine word */
346
347 if (BITS != (sizeof(N_word) << 3)) return(ErrCode_Bits);
348
349 if (BITS < 16) return(ErrCode_Word);
350
351 LONGBITS = 1;
352 while (longsample <<= 1) LONGBITS++; /* = # of bits in an unsigned long */
353
354 if (BITS > LONGBITS) return(ErrCode_Long);
355
356 LOGBITS = 0;
357 sample = BITS;
358 lsb = (sample AND LSB);
359 while ((sample >>= 1) and (not lsb))
360 {
361 LOGBITS++;
362 lsb = (sample AND LSB);
363 }
364
365 if (sample) return(ErrCode_Powr); /* # of bits is not a power of 2! */
366
367 if (BITS != (LSB << LOGBITS)) return(ErrCode_Loga);
368
369 MODMASK = BITS - 1;
370 FACTOR = LOGBITS - 3; /* ld(BITS / 8) = ld(BITS) - ld(8) = ld(BITS) - 3 */
371 MSB = (LSB << MODMASK);
372
373 BITMASKTAB = (wordptr) yasm_xmalloc((size_t) (BITS << FACTOR));
374
375 if (BITMASKTAB == NULL) return(ErrCode_Null);
376
377 for ( sample = 0; sample < BITS; sample++ )
378 {
379 BITMASKTAB[sample] = (LSB << sample);
380 }
381
382 LOG10 = (N_word) (MODMASK * 0.30103); /* = (BITS - 1) * ( ln 2 / ln 10 ) */
383 EXP10 = power10(LOG10);
384
385 return(ErrCode_Ok);
386}
387
388void BitVector_Shutdown(void)
389{
390 if (BITMASKTAB) yasm_xfree(BITMASKTAB);
391}

393N_word BitVector_Size(N_int bits) /* bit vector size (# of words) */
394{
395 N_word size;
396
397 size = bits >> LOGBITS;
398 if (bits AND MODMASK) size++;
399 return(size);
400}
401
402N_word BitVector_Mask(N_int bits) /* bit vector mask (unused bits) */
403{
404 N_word mask;
405
406 mask = bits AND MODMASK;
407 if (mask) mask = (N_word) ~(~0L << mask); else mask = (N_word) ~0L;
408 return(mask);
409}

443void BitVector_Destroy(wordptr addr) /* free bitvec */
444{
445 if (addr != NULL)
446 {
447 addr -= BIT_VECTOR_HIDDEN_WORDS;
448 yasm_xfree((voidptr) addr);
449 }
450}
451
452void BitVector_Destroy_List(listptr list, N_int count) /* free list */
453{
454 listptr slot;
455
456 if (list != NULL)
457 {
458 slot = list;
459 while (count-- > 0)
460 {
461 BitVector_Destroy(*slot++);
462 }
463 free((voidptr) list);
464 }
465}
466
467wordptr BitVector_Create(N_int bits, boolean clear) /* malloc */
468{
469 N_word size;
470 N_word mask;
471 N_word bytes;
472 wordptr addr;
473 wordptr zero;
474
475 size = BitVector_Size(bits);
476 mask = BitVector_Mask(bits);
477 bytes = (size + BIT_VECTOR_HIDDEN_WORDS) << FACTOR;
478 addr = (wordptr) yasm_xmalloc((size_t) bytes);
479 if (addr != NULL)
480 {
481 *addr++ = bits;
482 *addr++ = size;
483 *addr++ = mask;
484 if (clear)
485 {
486 zero = addr;
487 BIT_VECTOR_ZERO_WORDS(zero,size)
488 }
489 }
490 return(addr);
491}
492
493listptr BitVector_Create_List(N_int bits, boolean clear, N_int count)
494{
495 listptr list = NULL;
496 listptr slot;
497 wordptr addr;
498 N_int i;
499
500 if (count > 0)
501 {
502 list = (listptr) malloc(sizeof(wordptr) * count);
503 if (list != NULL)
504 {
505 slot = list;
506 for ( i = 0; i < count; i++ )
507 {
508 addr = BitVector_Create(bits,clear);
509 if (addr == NULL)
510 {
511 BitVector_Destroy_List(list,i);
512 return(NULL);
513 }
514 *slot++ = addr;
515 }
516 }
517 }
518 return(list);
519}

521wordptr BitVector_Resize(wordptr oldaddr, N_int bits) /* realloc */
522{
523 N_word bytes;
524 N_word oldsize;
525 N_word oldmask;
526 N_word newsize;
527 N_word newmask;
528 wordptr newaddr;
529 wordptr source;
530 wordptr target;
531
532 oldsize = size_(oldaddr);
533 oldmask = mask_(oldaddr);
534 newsize = BitVector_Size(bits);
535 newmask = BitVector_Mask(bits);
536 if (oldsize > 0) *(oldaddr+oldsize-1) &= oldmask;
537 if (newsize <= oldsize)
538 {
539 newaddr = oldaddr;
540 bits_(newaddr) = bits;
541 size_(newaddr) = newsize;
542 mask_(newaddr) = newmask;
543 if (newsize > 0) *(newaddr+newsize-1) &= newmask;
544 }
545 else
546 {
547 bytes = (newsize + BIT_VECTOR_HIDDEN_WORDS) << FACTOR;
548 newaddr = (wordptr) yasm_xmalloc((size_t) bytes);
549 if (newaddr != NULL)
550 {
551 *newaddr++ = bits;
552 *newaddr++ = newsize;
553 *newaddr++ = newmask;
554 target = newaddr;
555 source = oldaddr;
556 newsize -= oldsize;
557 BIT_VECTOR_COPY_WORDS(target,source,oldsize)
558 BIT_VECTOR_ZERO_WORDS(target,newsize)
559 }
560 BitVector_Destroy(oldaddr);
561 }
562 return(newaddr);
563}

565wordptr BitVector_Shadow(wordptr addr) /* makes new, same size but empty */
566{
567 return( BitVector_Create(bits_(addr),true) );

570wordptr BitVector_Clone(wordptr addr) /* makes exact duplicate */
571{
572 N_word bits;
573 wordptr twin;
574
575 bits = bits_(addr);
576 twin = BitVector_Create(bits,false);
577 if ((twin != NULL) and (bits > 0))
578 BIT_VECTOR_cpy_words(twin,addr,size_(addr));
579 return(twin);
580}

582wordptr BitVector_Concat(wordptr X, wordptr Y) /* returns concatenation */
583{
584 /* BEWARE that X = most significant part, Y = least significant part! */
585
586 N_word bitsX;
587 N_word bitsY;
588 N_word bitsZ;
589 wordptr Z;
590
591 bitsX = bits_(X);
592 bitsY = bits_(Y);
593 bitsZ = bitsX + bitsY;
594 Z = BitVector_Create(bitsZ,false);
595 if ((Z != NULL) and (bitsZ > 0))
596 {
597 BIT_VECTOR_cpy_words(Z,Y,size_(Y));
598 BitVector_Interval_Copy(Z,X,bitsY,0,bitsX);
599 *(Z+size_(Z)-1) &= mask_(Z);
600 }
601 return(Z);
602}
603
604void BitVector_Copy(wordptr X, wordptr Y) /* X = Y */
605{
606 N_word sizeX = size_(X);
607 N_word sizeY = size_(Y);
608 N_word maskX = mask_(X);
609 N_word maskY = mask_(Y);
610 N_word fill = 0;
611 wordptr lastX;
612 wordptr lastY;
613
614 if ((X != Y) and (sizeX > 0))
615 {
616 lastX = X + sizeX - 1;
617 if (sizeY > 0)
618 {
619 lastY = Y + sizeY - 1;
620 if ( (*lastY AND (maskY AND NOT (maskY >> 1))) == 0 ) *lastY &= maskY;
621 else
622 {
623 fill = (N_word) ~0L;
624 *lastY |= NOT maskY;
625 }
626 while ((sizeX > 0) and (sizeY > 0))
627 {
628 *X++ = *Y++;
629 sizeX--;
630 sizeY--;
631 }
632 *lastY &= maskY;
633 }
634 while (sizeX-- > 0) *X++ = fill;
635 *lastX &= maskX;
636 }
637}
638
639void BitVector_Empty(wordptr addr) /* X = {} clr all */
640{
641 N_word size = size_(addr);
642
643 BIT_VECTOR_ZERO_WORDS(addr,size)
644}
645
646void BitVector_Fill(wordptr addr) /* X = ~{} set all */
647{
648 N_word size = size_(addr);
649 N_word mask = mask_(addr);
650 N_word fill = (N_word) ~0L;
651
652 if (size > 0)
653 {
654 BIT_VECTOR_FILL_WORDS(addr,fill,size)
655 *(--addr) &= mask;
656 }
657}
658
659void BitVector_Flip(wordptr addr) /* X = ~X flip all */
660{
661 N_word size = size_(addr);
662 N_word mask = mask_(addr);
663 N_word flip = (N_word) ~0L;
664
665 if (size > 0)
666 {
667 BIT_VECTOR_FLIP_WORDS(addr,flip,size)
668 *(--addr) &= mask;
669 }
670}
671
672void BitVector_Primes(wordptr addr)
673{
674 N_word bits = bits_(addr);
675 N_word size = size_(addr);
676 wordptr work;
677 N_word temp;
678 N_word i,j;
679
680 if (size > 0)
681 {
682 temp = 0xAAAA;
683 i = BITS >> 4;
684 while (--i > 0)
685 {
686 temp <<= 16;
687 temp |= 0xAAAA;
688 }
689 i = size;
690 work = addr;
691 *work++ = temp XOR 0x0006;
692 while (--i > 0) *work++ = temp;
693 for ( i = 3; (j = i * i) < bits; i += 2 )
694 {
695 for ( ; j < bits; j += i ) BIT_VECTOR_CLR_BIT(addr,j)
696 }
697 *(addr+size-1) &= mask_(addr);
698 }
699}
700
701void BitVector_Reverse(wordptr X, wordptr Y)
702{
703 N_word bits = bits_(X);
704 N_word mask;
705 N_word bit;
706 N_word value;
707
708 if (bits > 0)
709 {
710 if (X == Y) BitVector_Interval_Reverse(X,0,bits-1);
711 else if (bits == bits_(Y))
712 {
713/* mask = mask_(Y); */
714/* mask &= NOT (mask >> 1); */
715 mask = BITMASKTAB[(bits-1) AND MODMASK];
716 Y += size_(Y) - 1;
717 value = 0;
718 bit = LSB;
719 while (bits-- > 0)
720 {
721 if ((*Y AND mask) != 0)
722 {
723 value |= bit;
724 }
725 if (not (mask >>= 1))
726 {
727 Y--;
728 mask = MSB;
729 }
730 if (not (bit <<= 1))
731 {
732 *X++ = value;
733 value = 0;
734 bit = LSB;
735 }
736 }
737 if (bit > LSB) *X = value;
738 }
739 }
740}
741
742void BitVector_Interval_Empty(wordptr addr, N_int lower, N_int upper)
743{ /* X = X \ [lower..upper] */
744 N_word bits = bits_(addr);
745 N_word size = size_(addr);
746 wordptr loaddr;
747 wordptr hiaddr;
748 N_word lobase;
749 N_word hibase;
750 N_word lomask;
751 N_word himask;
752 N_word diff;
753
754 if ((size > 0) and (lower < bits) and (upper < bits) and (lower <= upper))
755 {
756 lobase = lower >> LOGBITS;
757 hibase = upper >> LOGBITS;
758 diff = hibase - lobase;
759 loaddr = addr + lobase;
760 hiaddr = addr + hibase;
761
762 lomask = (N_word) (~0L << (lower AND MODMASK));
763 himask = (N_word) ~((~0L << (upper AND MODMASK)) << 1);
764
765 if (diff == 0)
766 {
767 *loaddr &= NOT (lomask AND himask);
768 }
769 else
770 {
771 *loaddr++ &= NOT lomask;
772 while (--diff > 0)
773 {
774 *loaddr++ = 0;
775 }
776 *hiaddr &= NOT himask;
777 }
778 }
779}

781void BitVector_Interval_Fill(wordptr addr, N_int lower, N_int upper)
782{ /* X = X + [lower..upper] */
783 N_word bits = bits_(addr);
784 N_word size = size_(addr);
785 N_word fill = (N_word) ~0L;
786 wordptr loaddr;
787 wordptr hiaddr;
788 N_word lobase;
789 N_word hibase;
790 N_word lomask;
791 N_word himask;
792 N_word diff;
793
794 if ((size > 0) and (lower < bits) and (upper < bits) and (lower <= upper))
795 {
796 lobase = lower >> LOGBITS;
797 hibase = upper >> LOGBITS;
798 diff = hibase - lobase;
799 loaddr = addr + lobase;
800 hiaddr = addr + hibase;
801
802 lomask = (N_word) (~0L << (lower AND MODMASK));
803 himask = (N_word) ~((~0L << (upper AND MODMASK)) << 1);
804
805 if (diff == 0)
806 {
807 *loaddr |= (lomask AND himask);
808 }
809 else
810 {
811 *loaddr++ |= lomask;
812 while (--diff > 0)
813 {
814 *loaddr++ = fill;
815 }
816 *hiaddr |= himask;
817 }
818 *(addr+size-1) &= mask_(addr);
819 }
820}

822void BitVector_Interval_Flip(wordptr addr, N_int lower, N_int upper)
823{ /* X = X ^ [lower..upper] */
824 N_word bits = bits_(addr);
825 N_word size = size_(addr);
826 N_word flip = (N_word) ~0L;
827 wordptr loaddr;
828 wordptr hiaddr;
829 N_word lobase;
830 N_word hibase;
831 N_word lomask;
832 N_word himask;
833 N_word diff;
834
835 if ((size > 0) and (lower < bits) and (upper < bits) and (lower <= upper))
836 {
837 lobase = lower >> LOGBITS;
838 hibase = upper >> LOGBITS;
839 diff = hibase - lobase;
840 loaddr = addr + lobase;
841 hiaddr = addr + hibase;
842
843 lomask = (N_word) (~0L << (lower AND MODMASK));
844 himask = (N_word) ~((~0L << (upper AND MODMASK)) << 1);
845
846 if (diff == 0)
847 {
848 *loaddr ^= (lomask AND himask);
849 }
850 else
851 {
852 *loaddr++ ^= lomask;
853 while (--diff > 0)
854 {
855 *loaddr++ ^= flip;
856 }
857 *hiaddr ^= himask;
858 }
859 *(addr+size-1) &= mask_(addr);
860 }

862
863void BitVector_Interval_Reverse(wordptr addr, N_int lower, N_int upper)
864{
865 N_word bits = bits_(addr);
866 wordptr loaddr;
867 wordptr hiaddr;
868 N_word lomask;
869 N_word himask;
870
871 if ((bits > 0) and (lower < bits) and (upper < bits) and (lower < upper))
872 {
873 loaddr = addr + (lower >> LOGBITS);
874 hiaddr = addr + (upper >> LOGBITS);
875 lomask = BITMASKTAB[lower AND MODMASK];
876 himask = BITMASKTAB[upper AND MODMASK];
877 for ( bits = upper - lower + 1; bits > 1; bits -= 2 )
878 {
879 if (((*loaddr AND lomask) != 0) XOR ((*hiaddr AND himask) != 0))
880 {
881 *loaddr ^= lomask; /* swap bits only if they differ! */
882 *hiaddr ^= himask;
883 }
884 if (not (lomask <<= 1))
885 {
886 lomask = LSB;
887 loaddr++;
888 }
889 if (not (himask >>= 1))
890 {
891 himask = MSB;
892 hiaddr--;
893 }
894 }
895 }
896}
897
898boolean BitVector_interval_scan_inc(wordptr addr, N_int start,
899 N_intptr min, N_intptr max)
900{
901 N_word size = size_(addr);
902 N_word mask = mask_(addr);
903 N_word offset;
904 N_word bitmask;
905 N_word value;
906 boolean empty;
907
908 if ((size == 0) or (start >= bits_(addr))) return(FALSE);
909
910 *min = start;
911 *max = start;
912
913 offset = start >> LOGBITS;
914
915 *(addr+size-1) &= mask;
916
917 addr += offset;
918 size -= offset;
919
920 bitmask = BITMASKTAB[start AND MODMASK];
921 mask = NOT (bitmask OR (bitmask - 1));
922
923 value = *addr++;
924 if ((value AND bitmask) == 0)
925 {
926 value &= mask;
927 if (value == 0)
928 {
929 offset++;
930 empty = TRUE;
931 while (empty and (--size > 0))
932 {
933 if ((value = *addr++)) empty = false; else offset++;
934 }
935 if (empty) return(FALSE);
936 }
937 start = offset << LOGBITS;
938 bitmask = LSB;
939 mask = value;
940 while (not (mask AND LSB))
941 {
942 bitmask <<= 1;
943 mask >>= 1;
944 start++;
945 }
946 mask = NOT (bitmask OR (bitmask - 1));
947 *min = start;
948 *max = start;
949 }
950 value = NOT value;
951 value &= mask;
952 if (value == 0)
953 {
954 offset++;
955 empty = TRUE;
956 while (empty and (--size > 0))
957 {
958 if ((value = NOT *addr++)) empty = false; else offset++;
959 }
960 if (empty) value = LSB;
961 }
962 start = offset << LOGBITS;
963 while (not (value AND LSB))
964 {
965 value >>= 1;
966 start++;
967 }
968 *max = --start;
969 return(TRUE);
970}
971
972boolean BitVector_interval_scan_dec(wordptr addr, N_int start,
973 N_intptr min, N_intptr max)
974{
975 N_word size = size_(addr);
976 N_word mask = mask_(addr);
977 N_word offset;
978 N_word bitmask;
979 N_word value;
980 boolean empty;
981
982 if ((size == 0) or (start >= bits_(addr))) return(FALSE);
983
984 *min = start;
985 *max = start;
986
987 offset = start >> LOGBITS;
988
989 if (offset >= size) return(FALSE);
990
991 *(addr+size-1) &= mask;
992
993 addr += offset;
994 size = ++offset;
995
996 bitmask = BITMASKTAB[start AND MODMASK];
997 mask = (bitmask - 1);
998
999 value = *addr--;
1000 if ((value AND bitmask) == 0)
1001 {
1002 value &= mask;
1003 if (value == 0)
1004 {
1005 offset--;
1006 empty = TRUE;
1007 while (empty and (--size > 0))
1008 {
1009 if ((value = *addr--)) empty = false; else offset--;
1010 }
1011 if (empty) return(FALSE);
1012 }
1013 start = offset << LOGBITS;
1014 bitmask = MSB;
1015 mask = value;
1016 while (not (mask AND MSB))
1017 {
1018 bitmask >>= 1;
1019 mask <<= 1;
1020 start--;
1021 }
1022 mask = (bitmask - 1);
1023 *max = --start;
1024 *min = start;
1025 }
1026 value = NOT value;
1027 value &= mask;
1028 if (value == 0)
1029 {
1030 offset--;
1031 empty = TRUE;
1032 while (empty and (--size > 0))
1033 {
1034 if ((value = NOT *addr--)) empty = false; else offset--;
1035 }
1036 if (empty) value = MSB;
1037 }
1038 start = offset << LOGBITS;
1039 while (not (value AND MSB))
1040 {
1041 value <<= 1;
1042 start--;
1043 }
1044 *min = start;
1045 return(TRUE);
1046}
1047
1048void BitVector_Interval_Copy(wordptr X, wordptr Y, N_int Xoffset,
1049 N_int Yoffset, N_int length)
1050{
1051 N_word bitsX = bits_(X);
1052 N_word bitsY = bits_(Y);
1053 N_word source = 0; /* silence compiler warning */
1054 N_word target = 0; /* silence compiler warning */
1055 N_word s_lo_base;
1056 N_word s_hi_base;
1057 N_word s_lo_bit;
1058 N_word s_hi_bit;
1059 N_word s_base;
1060 N_word s_lower = 0; /* silence compiler warning */
1061 N_word s_upper = 0; /* silence compiler warning */
1062 N_word s_bits;
1063 N_word s_min;
1064 N_word s_max;
1065 N_word t_lo_base;
1066 N_word t_hi_base;
1067 N_word t_lo_bit;
1068 N_word t_hi_bit;
1069 N_word t_base;
1070 N_word t_lower = 0; /* silence compiler warning */
1071 N_word t_upper = 0; /* silence compiler warning */
1072 N_word t_bits;
1073 N_word t_min;
1074 N_word mask;
1075 N_word bits;
1076 N_word sel;
1077 boolean ascending;
1078 boolean notfirst;
1079 wordptr Z = X;
1080
1081 if ((length > 0) and (Xoffset < bitsX) and (Yoffset < bitsY))
1082 {
1083 if ((Xoffset + length) > bitsX) length = bitsX - Xoffset;
1084 if ((Yoffset + length) > bitsY) length = bitsY - Yoffset;
1085
1086 ascending = (Xoffset <= Yoffset);
1087
1088 s_lo_base = Yoffset >> LOGBITS;
1089 s_lo_bit = Yoffset AND MODMASK;
1090 Yoffset += --length;
1091 s_hi_base = Yoffset >> LOGBITS;
1092 s_hi_bit = Yoffset AND MODMASK;
1093
1094 t_lo_base = Xoffset >> LOGBITS;
1095 t_lo_bit = Xoffset AND MODMASK;
1096 Xoffset += length;
1097 t_hi_base = Xoffset >> LOGBITS;
1098 t_hi_bit = Xoffset AND MODMASK;
1099
1100 if (ascending)
1101 {
1102 s_base = s_lo_base;
1103 t_base = t_lo_base;
1104 }
1105 else
1106 {
1107 s_base = s_hi_base;
1108 t_base = t_hi_base;
1109 }
1110 s_bits = 0;
1111 t_bits = 0;
1112 Y += s_base;
1113 X += t_base;
1114 notfirst = FALSE;
1115 while (TRUE)
1116 {
1117 if (t_bits == 0)
1118 {
1119 if (notfirst)
1120 {
1121 *X = target;
1122 if (ascending)
1123 {
1124 if (t_base == t_hi_base) break;
1125 t_base++;
1126 X++;
1127 }
1128 else
1129 {
1130 if (t_base == t_lo_base) break;
1131 t_base--;
1132 X--;
1133 }
1134 }
1135 sel = ((t_base == t_hi_base) << 1) OR (t_base == t_lo_base);
1136 switch (sel)
1137 {
1138 case 0:
1139 t_lower = 0;
1140 t_upper = BITS - 1;
1141 t_bits = BITS;
1142 target = 0;
1143 break;
1144 case 1:
1145 t_lower = t_lo_bit;
1146 t_upper = BITS - 1;
1147 t_bits = BITS - t_lo_bit;
1148 mask = (N_word) (~0L << t_lower);
1149 target = *X AND NOT mask;
1150 break;
1151 case 2:
1152 t_lower = 0;
1153 t_upper = t_hi_bit;
1154 t_bits = t_hi_bit + 1;
1155 mask = (N_word) ((~0L << t_upper) << 1);
1156 target = *X AND mask;
1157 break;
1158 case 3:
1159 t_lower = t_lo_bit;
1160 t_upper = t_hi_bit;
1161 t_bits = t_hi_bit - t_lo_bit + 1;
1162 mask = (N_word) (~0L << t_lower);
1163 mask &= (N_word) ~((~0L << t_upper) << 1);
1164 target = *X AND NOT mask;
1165 break;
1166 }
1167 }
1168 if (s_bits == 0)
1169 {
1170 if (notfirst)
1171 {
1172 if (ascending)
1173 {
1174 if (s_base == s_hi_base) break;
1175 s_base++;
1176 Y++;
1177 }
1178 else
1179 {
1180 if (s_base == s_lo_base) break;
1181 s_base--;
1182 Y--;
1183 }
1184 }
1185 source = *Y;
1186 sel = ((s_base == s_hi_base) << 1) OR (s_base == s_lo_base);
1187 switch (sel)
1188 {
1189 case 0:
1190 s_lower = 0;
1191 s_upper = BITS - 1;
1192 s_bits = BITS;
1193 break;
1194 case 1:
1195 s_lower = s_lo_bit;
1196 s_upper = BITS - 1;
1197 s_bits = BITS - s_lo_bit;
1198 break;
1199 case 2:
1200 s_lower = 0;
1201 s_upper = s_hi_bit;
1202 s_bits = s_hi_bit + 1;
1203 break;
1204 case 3:
1205 s_lower = s_lo_bit;
1206 s_upper = s_hi_bit;
1207 s_bits = s_hi_bit - s_lo_bit + 1;
1208 break;
1209 }
1210 }
1211 notfirst = TRUE;
1212 if (s_bits > t_bits)
1213 {
1214 bits = t_bits - 1;
1215 if (ascending)
1216 {
1217 s_min = s_lower;
1218 s_max = s_lower + bits;
1219 }
1220 else
1221 {
1222 s_max = s_upper;
1223 s_min = s_upper - bits;
1224 }
1225 t_min = t_lower;
1226 }
1227 else
1228 {
1229 bits = s_bits - 1;
1230 if (ascending) t_min = t_lower;
1231 else t_min = t_upper - bits;
1232 s_min = s_lower;
1233 s_max = s_upper;
1234 }
1235 bits++;
1236 mask = (N_word) (~0L << s_min);
1237 mask &= (N_word) ~((~0L << s_max) << 1);
1238 if (s_min == t_min) target |= (source AND mask);
1239 else
1240 {
1241 if (s_min < t_min) target |= (source AND mask) << (t_min-s_min);
1242 else target |= (source AND mask) >> (s_min-t_min);
1243 }
1244 if (ascending)
1245 {
1246 s_lower += bits;
1247 t_lower += bits;
1248 }
1249 else
1250 {
1251 s_upper -= bits;
1252 t_upper -= bits;
1253 }
1254 s_bits -= bits;
1255 t_bits -= bits;
1256 }
1257 *(Z+size_(Z)-1) &= mask_(Z);
1258 }
1259}

1261
1262wordptr BitVector_Interval_Substitute(wordptr X, wordptr Y,
1263 N_int Xoffset, N_int Xlength,
1264 N_int Yoffset, N_int Ylength)
1265{
1266 N_word Xbits = bits_(X);
1267 N_word Ybits = bits_(Y);
1268 N_word limit;
1269 N_word diff;
1270
1271 if ((Xoffset <= Xbits) and (Yoffset <= Ybits))
1272 {
1273 limit = Xoffset + Xlength;
1274 if (limit > Xbits)
1275 {
1276 limit = Xbits;
1277 Xlength = Xbits - Xoffset;
1278 }
1279 if ((Yoffset + Ylength) > Ybits)
1280 {
1281 Ylength = Ybits - Yoffset;
1282 }
1283 if (Xlength == Ylength)
1284 {
1285 if ((Ylength > 0) and ((X != Y) or (Xoffset != Yoffset)))
1286 {
1287 BitVector_Interval_Copy(X,Y,Xoffset,Yoffset,Ylength);
1288 }
1289 }
1290 else /* Xlength != Ylength */
1291 {
1292 if (Xlength > Ylength)
1293 {
1294 diff = Xlength - Ylength;
1295 if (Ylength > 0) BitVector_Interval_Copy(X,Y,Xoffset,Yoffset,Ylength);
1296 if (limit < Xbits) BitVector_Delete(X,Xoffset+Ylength,diff,FALSE);
1297 if ((X = BitVector_Resize(X,Xbits-diff)) == NULL) return(NULL);
1298 }
1299 else /* Ylength > Xlength ==> Ylength > 0 */
1300 {
1301 diff = Ylength - Xlength;
1302 if (X != Y)
1303 {
1304 if ((X = BitVector_Resize(X,Xbits+diff)) == NULL) return(NULL);
1305 if (limit < Xbits) BitVector_Insert(X,limit,diff,FALSE);
1306 BitVector_Interval_Copy(X,Y,Xoffset,Yoffset,Ylength);
1307 }
1308 else /* in-place */
1309 {
1310 if ((Y = X = BitVector_Resize(X,Xbits+diff)) == NULL) return(NULL);
1311 if (limit >= Xbits)
1312 {
1313 BitVector_Interval_Copy(X,Y,Xoffset,Yoffset,Ylength);
1314 }
1315 else /* limit < Xbits */
1316 {
1317 BitVector_Insert(X,limit,diff,FALSE);
1318 if ((Yoffset+Ylength) <= limit)
1319 {
1320 BitVector_Interval_Copy(X,Y,Xoffset,Yoffset,Ylength);
1321 }
1322 else /* overlaps or lies above critical area */
1323 {
1324 if (limit <= Yoffset)
1325 {
1326 Yoffset += diff;
1327 BitVector_Interval_Copy(X,Y,Xoffset,Yoffset,Ylength);
1328 }
1329 else /* Yoffset < limit */
1330 {
1331 Xlength = limit - Yoffset;
1332 BitVector_Interval_Copy(X,Y,Xoffset,Yoffset,Xlength);
1333 Yoffset = Xoffset + Ylength; /* = limit + diff */
1334 Xoffset += Xlength;
1335 Ylength -= Xlength;
1336 BitVector_Interval_Copy(X,Y,Xoffset,Yoffset,Ylength);
1337 }
1338 }
1339 }
1340 }
1341 }
1342 }
1343 }
1344 return(X);
1345}

1347boolean BitVector_is_empty(wordptr addr) /* X == {} ? */
1348{
1349 N_word size = size_(addr);
1350 boolean r = TRUE;
1351
1352 if (size > 0)
1353 {
1354 *(addr+size-1) &= mask_(addr);
1355 while (r and (size-- > 0)) r = ( *addr++ == 0 );
1356 }
1357 return(r);
1358}

1360boolean BitVector_is_full(wordptr addr) /* X == ~{} ? */
1361{
1362 N_word size = size_(addr);
1363 N_word mask = mask_(addr);
1364 boolean r = FALSE;
1365 wordptr last;
1366
1367 if (size > 0)
1368 {
1369 r = TRUE;
1370 last = addr + size - 1;
1371 *last |= NOT mask;
1372 while (r and (size-- > 0)) r = ( NOT *addr++ == 0 );
1373 *last &= mask;
1374 }
1375 return(r);
1376}

1378boolean BitVector_equal(wordptr X, wordptr Y) /* X == Y ? */
1379{
1380 N_word size = size_(X);
1381 N_word mask = mask_(X);
1382 boolean r = FALSE;
1383

1385 {
1386 r = TRUE;
1387 if (size > 0)
1388 {
1389 *(X+size-1) &= mask;
1390 *(Y+size-1) &= mask;
1391 while (r and (size-- > 0)) r = (*X++ == *Y++);
1392 }
1393 }
1394 return(r);
1395}

1397Z_int BitVector_Lexicompare(wordptr X, wordptr Y) /* X <,=,> Y ? */
1398{ /* unsigned */
1399 N_word bitsX = bits_(X);
1400 N_word bitsY = bits_(Y);
1401 N_word size = size_(X);
1402 boolean r = TRUE;
1403
1404 if (bitsX == bitsY)
1405 {
1406 if (size > 0)
1407 {
1408 X += size;
1409 Y += size;
1410 while (r and (size-- > 0)) r = (*(--X) == *(--Y));
1411 }
1412 if (r) return((Z_int) 0);
1413 else
1414 {
1415 if (*X < *Y) return((Z_int) -1); else return((Z_int) 1);
1416 }
1417 }
1418 else
1419 {
1420 if (bitsX < bitsY) return((Z_int) -1); else return((Z_int) 1);
1421 }
1422}
1423
1424Z_int BitVector_Compare(wordptr X, wordptr Y) /* X <,=,> Y ? */
1425{ /* signed */
1426 N_word bitsX = bits_(X);
1427 N_word bitsY = bits_(Y);
1428 N_word size = size_(X);
1429 N_word mask = mask_(X);
1430 N_word sign;
1431 boolean r = TRUE;
1432
1433 if (bitsX == bitsY)
1434 {
1435 if (size > 0)
1436 {
1437 X += size;
1438 Y += size;
1439 mask &= NOT (mask >> 1);
1440 if ((sign = (*(X-1) AND mask)) != (*(Y-1) AND mask))
1441 {
1442 if (sign) return((Z_int) -1); else return((Z_int) 1);
1443 }
1444 while (r and (size-- > 0)) r = (*(--X) == *(--Y));
1445 }
1446 if (r) return((Z_int) 0);
1447 else
1448 {
1449 if (*X < *Y) return((Z_int) -1); else return((Z_int) 1);
1450 }
1451 }
1452 else
1453 {
1454 if (bitsX < bitsY) return((Z_int) -1); else return((Z_int) 1);
1455 }
1456}

1458charptr BitVector_to_Hex(wordptr addr)
1459{
1460 N_word bits = bits_(addr);
1461 N_word size = size_(addr);
1462 N_word value;
1463 N_word count;
1464 N_word digit;
1465 N_word length;
1466 charptr string;
1467
1468 length = bits >> 2;
1469 if (bits AND 0x0003) length++;
1470 string = (charptr) yasm_xmalloc((size_t) (length+1));
1471 if (string == NULL) return(NULL);
1472 string += length;
1473 *string = (N_char) '\0';
1474 if (size > 0)
1475 {
1476 *(addr+size-1) &= mask_(addr);
1477 while ((size-- > 0) and (length > 0))
1478 {
1479 value = *addr++;
1480 count = BITS >> 2;
1481 while ((count-- > 0) and (length > 0))
1482 {
1483 digit = value AND 0x000F;
1484 if (digit > 9) digit += (N_word) 'A' - 10;
1485 else digit += (N_word) '0';
1486 *(--string) = (N_char) digit; length--;
1487 if ((count > 0) and (length > 0)) value >>= 4;
1488 }
1489 }
1490 }
1491 return(string);
1492}
1493
1494ErrCode BitVector_from_Hex(wordptr addr, charptr string)
1495{
1496 N_word size = size_(addr);
1497 N_word mask = mask_(addr);
1498 boolean ok = TRUE;
1499 size_t length;
1500 N_word value;
1501 N_word count;
1502 int digit;
1503
1504 if (size > 0)
1505 {
1506 length = strlen((char *) string);
1507 string += length;
1508 while (size-- > 0)
1509 {
1510 value = 0;
1511 for ( count = 0; (ok and (length > 0) and (count < BITS)); count += 4 )
1512 {
1513 digit = (int) *(--string); length--;
1514 /* separate because toupper() is likely a macro! */
1515 digit = toupper(digit);
1516 if (digit == '_')
1517 count -= 4;
1518 else if ((ok = (isxdigit(digit) != 0)))
1519 {
1520 if (digit >= (int) 'A') digit -= (int) 'A' - 10;
1521 else digit -= (int) '0';
1522 value |= (((N_word) digit) << count);
1523 }
1524 }
1525 *addr++ = value;
1526 }
1527 *(--addr) &= mask;
1528 }
1529 if (ok) return(ErrCode_Ok);
1530 else return(ErrCode_Pars);
1531}

1533ErrCode BitVector_from_Oct(wordptr addr, charptr string)
1534{
1535 N_word size = size_(addr);
1536 N_word mask = mask_(addr);
1537 boolean ok = TRUE;
1538 size_t length;
1539 N_word value;
1540 N_word value_fill = 0;
1541 N_word count;
1542 Z_word count_fill = 0;
1543 int digit = 0;
1544
1545 if (size > 0)
1546 {
1547 length = strlen((char *) string);
1548 string += length;
1549 while (size-- > 0)
1550 {
1551 value = value_fill;
1552 for ( count = count_fill; (ok and (length > 0) and (count < BITS)); count += 3 )
1553 {
1554 digit = (int) *(--string); length--;
1555 if (digit == '_')
1556 count -= 3;
1557 else if ((ok = (isdigit(digit) && digit != '8' && digit != '9')) != 0)
1558 {
1559 digit -= (int) '0';
1560 value |= (((N_word) digit) << count);
1561 }
1562 }
1563 count_fill = (Z_word)count-(Z_word)BITS;
1564 if (count_fill > 0)
1565 value_fill = (((N_word) digit) >> (3-count_fill));
1566 else
1567 value_fill = 0;
1568 *addr++ = value;
1569 }
1570 *(--addr) &= mask;
1571 }
1572 if (ok) return(ErrCode_Ok);
1573 else return(ErrCode_Pars);
1574}

1576charptr BitVector_to_Bin(wordptr addr)
1577{
1578 N_word size = size_(addr);
1579 N_word value;
1580 N_word count;
1581 N_word digit;
1582 N_word length;
1583 charptr string;
1584
1585 length = bits_(addr);
1586 string = (charptr) yasm_xmalloc((size_t) (length+1));
1587 if (string == NULL) return(NULL);
1588 string += length;
1589 *string = (N_char) '\0';
1590 if (size > 0)
1591 {
1592 *(addr+size-1) &= mask_(addr);
1593 while (size-- > 0)
1594 {
1595 value = *addr++;
1596 count = BITS;
1597 if (count > length) count = length;
1598 while (count-- > 0)
1599 {
1600 digit = value AND 0x0001;
1601 digit += (N_word) '0';
1602 *(--string) = (N_char) digit; length--;
1603 if (count > 0) value >>= 1;
1604 }
1605 }
1606 }
1607 return(string);
1608}

1653charptr BitVector_to_Dec(wordptr addr)
1654{
1655 N_word bits = bits_(addr);
1656 N_word length;
1657 N_word digits;
1658 N_word count;
1659 N_word q;
1660 N_word r;
1661 boolean loop;
1662 charptr result;
1663 charptr string;
1664 wordptr quot;
1665 wordptr rest;
1666 wordptr temp;
1667 wordptr base;
1668 Z_int sign;
1669
1670 length = (N_word) (bits / 3.3); /* digits = bits * ln(2) / ln(10) */
1671 length += 2; /* compensate for truncating & provide space for minus sign */
1672 result = (charptr) yasm_xmalloc((size_t) (length+1)); /* remember the '\0'! */
1673 if (result == NULL) return(NULL);
1674 string = result;
1675 sign = BitVector_Sign(addr);
1676 if ((bits < 4) or (sign == 0))
1677 {
1678 if (bits > 0) digits = *addr; else digits = (N_word) 0;
1679 if (sign < 0) digits = ((N_word)(-((Z_word)digits))) AND mask_(addr);
1680 *string++ = (N_char) digits + (N_char) '0';
1681 digits = 1;
1682 }
1683 else
1684 {
1685 quot = BitVector_Create(bits,FALSE);
1686 if (quot == NULL)
1687 {
1688 BitVector_Dispose(result);
1689 return(NULL);
1690 }
1691 rest = BitVector_Create(bits,FALSE);
1692 if (rest == NULL)
1693 {
1694 BitVector_Dispose(result);
1695 BitVector_Destroy(quot);
1696 return(NULL);
1697 }
1698 temp = BitVector_Create(bits,FALSE);
1699 if (temp == NULL)
1700 {
1701 BitVector_Dispose(result);
1702 BitVector_Destroy(quot);
1703 BitVector_Destroy(rest);
1704 return(NULL);
1705 }
1706 base = BitVector_Create(bits,TRUE);
1707 if (base == NULL)
1708 {
1709 BitVector_Dispose(result);
1710 BitVector_Destroy(quot);
1711 BitVector_Destroy(rest);
1712 BitVector_Destroy(temp);
1713 return(NULL);
1714 }
1715 if (sign < 0) BitVector_Negate(quot,addr);
1716 else BitVector_Copy(quot,addr);
1717 digits = 0;
1718 *base = EXP10;
1719 loop = (bits >= BITS);
1720 do
1721 {
1722 if (loop)
1723 {
1724 BitVector_Copy(temp,quot);
1725 if (BitVector_Div_Pos(quot,temp,base,rest))
1726 {
1727 BitVector_Dispose(result); /* emergency exit */
1728 BitVector_Destroy(quot);
1729 BitVector_Destroy(rest); /* should never occur */
1730 BitVector_Destroy(temp); /* under normal operation */
1731 BitVector_Destroy(base);
1732 return(NULL);
1733 }
1734 loop = not BitVector_is_empty(quot);
1735 q = *rest;
1736 }
1737 else q = *quot;
1738 count = LOG10;
1739 while (((loop and (count-- > 0)) or ((not loop) and (q != 0))) and
1740 (digits < length))
1741 {
1742 if (q != 0)
1743 {
1744 BIT_VECTOR_DIGITIZE(N_word,q,r)
1745 }
1746 else r = (N_word) '0';
1747 *string++ = (N_char) r;
1748 digits++;
1749 }
1750 }
1751 while (loop and (digits < length));
1752 BitVector_Destroy(quot);
1753 BitVector_Destroy(rest);
1754 BitVector_Destroy(temp);
1755 BitVector_Destroy(base);
1756 }
1757 if ((sign < 0) and (digits < length))
1758 {
1759 *string++ = (N_char) '-';
1760 digits++;
1761 }
1762 *string = (N_char) '\0';
1763 BIT_VECTOR_reverse(result,digits);
1764 return(result);
1765}

1810ErrCode BitVector_from_Dec_static(BitVector_from_Dec_static_data *data,
1811 wordptr addr, charptr string)
1812{
1813 ErrCode error = ErrCode_Ok;
1814 N_word bits = bits_(addr);
1815 N_word mask = mask_(addr);
1816 boolean init = (bits > BITS);
1817 boolean minus;
1818 boolean shift;
1819 boolean carry;
1820 wordptr term;
1821 wordptr base;
1822 wordptr prod;
1823 wordptr rank;
1824 wordptr temp;
1825 N_word accu;
1826 N_word powr;
1827 N_word count;
1828 size_t length;
1829 int digit;
1830
1831 if (bits > 0)
1832 {
1833 term = data->term;
1834 base = data->base;
1835 prod = data->prod;
1836 rank = data->rank;
1837 temp = data->temp;
1838
1839 length = strlen((char *) string);
1840 if (length == 0) return(ErrCode_Pars);
1841 digit = (int) *string;
1842 if ((minus = (digit == (int) '-')) or
1843 (digit == (int) '+'))
1844 {
1845 string++;
1846 if (--length == 0) return(ErrCode_Pars);
1847 }
1848 string += length;
1849 if (init)
1850 {
1851 BitVector_Empty(prod);
1852 BitVector_Empty(rank);
1853 }
1854 BitVector_Empty(addr);
1855 *base = EXP10;
1856 shift = FALSE;
1857 while ((not error) and (length > 0))
1858 {
1859 accu = 0;
1860 powr = 1;
1861 count = LOG10;
1862 while ((not error) and (length > 0) and (count-- > 0))
1863 {
1864 digit = (int) *(--string); length--;
1865 /* separate because isdigit() is likely a macro! */
1866 if (isdigit(digit) != 0)
1867 {
1868 accu += ((N_word) digit - (N_word) '0') * powr;
1869 powr *= 10;
1870 }
1871 else error = ErrCode_Pars;
1872 }
1873 if (not error)
1874 {
1875 if (shift)
1876 {
1877 *term = accu;
1878 BitVector_Copy(temp,rank);
1879 error = BitVector_Mul_Pos(prod,temp,term,FALSE);
1880 }
1881 else
1882 {
1883 *prod = accu;
1884 if ((not init) and ((accu AND NOT mask) != 0)) error = ErrCode_Ovfl;
1885 }
1886 if (not error)
1887 {
1888 carry = FALSE;
1889 BitVector_compute(addr,addr,prod,FALSE,&carry);
1890 /* ignores sign change (= overflow) but not */
1891 /* numbers too large (= carry) for resulting bit vector */
1892 if (carry) error = ErrCode_Ovfl;
1893 else
1894 {
1895 if (length > 0)
1896 {
1897 if (shift)
1898 {
1899 BitVector_Copy(temp,rank);
1900 error = BitVector_Mul_Pos(rank,temp,base,FALSE);
1901 }
1902 else
1903 {
1904 *rank = *base;
1905 shift = TRUE;
1906 }
1907 }
1908 }
1909 }
1910 }
1911 }
1912 if (not error and minus)
1913 {
1914 BitVector_Negate(addr,addr);
1915 if ((*(addr + size_(addr) - 1) AND mask AND NOT (mask >> 1)) == 0)
1916 error = ErrCode_Ovfl;
1917 }
1918 }
1919 return(error);
1920}

2062charptr BitVector_to_Enum(wordptr addr)
2063{
2064 N_word bits = bits_(addr);
2065 N_word sample;
2066 N_word length;
2067 N_word digits;
2068 N_word factor;
2069 N_word power;
2070 N_word start;
2071 N_word min;
2072 N_word max;
2073 charptr string;
2074 charptr target;
2075 boolean comma;
2076
2077 if (bits > 0)
2078 {
2079 sample = bits - 1; /* greatest possible index */
2080 length = 2; /* account for index 0 and terminating '\0' */
2081 digits = 1; /* account for intervening dashes and commas */
2082 factor = 1;
2083 power = 10;
2084 while (sample >= (power-1))
2085 {
2086 length += ++digits * factor * 6; /* 9,90,900,9000,... (9*2/3 = 6) */
2087 factor = power;
2088 power *= 10;
2089 }
2090 if (sample > --factor)
2091 {
2092 sample -= factor;
2093 factor = (N_word) ( sample / 3 );
2094 factor = (factor << 1) + (sample - (factor * 3));
2095 length += ++digits * factor;
2096 }
2097 }
2098 else length = 1;
2099 string = (charptr) yasm_xmalloc((size_t) length);
2100 if (string == NULL) return(NULL);
2101 start = 0;
2102 comma = FALSE;
2103 target = string;
2104 while ((start < bits) and BitVector_interval_scan_inc(addr,start,&min,&max))
2105 {
2106 start = max + 2;
2107 if (comma) *target++ = (N_char) ',';
2108 if (min == max)
2109 {
2110 target += BIT_VECTOR_int2str(target,min);
2111 }
2112 else
2113 {
2114 if (min+1 == max)
2115 {
2116 target += BIT_VECTOR_int2str(target,min);
2117 *target++ = (N_char) ',';
2118 target += BIT_VECTOR_int2str(target,max);
2119 }
2120 else
2121 {
2122 target += BIT_VECTOR_int2str(target,min);
2123 *target++ = (N_char) '-';
2124 target += BIT_VECTOR_int2str(target,max);
2125 }
2126 }
2127 comma = TRUE;
2128 }
2129 *target = (N_char) '\0';
2130 return(string);
2131}

2133ErrCode BitVector_from_Enum(wordptr addr, charptr string)
2134{
2135 ErrCode error = ErrCode_Ok;
2136 N_word bits = bits_(addr);
2137 N_word state = 1;
2138 N_word token;
2139 N_word indx = 0; /* silence compiler warning */
2140 N_word start = 0; /* silence compiler warning */
2141
2142 if (bits > 0)
2143 {
2144 BitVector_Empty(addr);
2145 while ((not error) and (state != 0))
2146 {
2147 token = (N_word) *string;
2148 /* separate because isdigit() is likely a macro! */
2149 if (isdigit((int)token) != 0)
2150 {
2151 string += BIT_VECTOR_str2int(string,&indx);
2152 if (indx < bits) token = (N_word) '0';
2153 else error = ErrCode_Indx;
2154 }
2155 else string++;
2156 if (not error)
2157 switch (state)
2158 {
2159 case 1:
2160 switch (token)
2161 {
2162 case (N_word) '0':
2163 state = 2;
2164 break;
2165 case (N_word) '\0':
2166 state = 0;
2167 break;
2168 default:
2169 error = ErrCode_Pars;
2170 break;
2171 }
2172 break;
2173 case 2:
2174 switch (token)
2175 {
2176 case (N_word) '-':
2177 start = indx;
2178 state = 3;
2179 break;
2180 case (N_word) ',':
2181 BIT_VECTOR_SET_BIT(addr,indx)
2182 state = 5;
2183 break;
2184 case (N_word) '\0':
2185 BIT_VECTOR_SET_BIT(addr,indx)
2186 state = 0;
2187 break;
2188 default:
2189 error = ErrCode_Pars;
2190 break;
2191 }
2192 break;
2193 case 3:
2194 switch (token)
2195 {
2196 case (N_word) '0':
2197 if (start < indx)
2198 BitVector_Interval_Fill(addr,start,indx);
2199 else if (start == indx)
2200 BIT_VECTOR_SET_BIT(addr,indx)
2201 else error = ErrCode_Ordr;
2202 state = 4;
2203 break;
2204 default:
2205 error = ErrCode_Pars;
2206 break;
2207 }
2208 break;
2209 case 4:
2210 switch (token)
2211 {
2212 case (N_word) ',':
2213 state = 5;
2214 break;
2215 case (N_word) '\0':
2216 state = 0;
2217 break;
2218 default:
2219 error = ErrCode_Pars;
2220 break;
2221 }
2222 break;
2223 case 5:
2224 switch (token)
2225 {
2226 case (N_word) '0':
2227 state = 2;
2228 break;
2229 default:
2230 error = ErrCode_Pars;
2231 break;
2232 }
2233 break;
2234 }
2235 }
2236 }
2237 return(error);
2238}

2311boolean BitVector_rotate_left(wordptr addr)
2312{
2313 N_word size = size_(addr);
2314 N_word mask = mask_(addr);
2315 N_word msb;
2316 boolean carry_in;
2317 boolean carry_out = FALSE;
2318
2319 if (size > 0)
2320 {
2321 msb = mask AND NOT (mask >> 1);
2322 carry_in = ((*(addr+size-1) AND msb) != 0);
2323 while (size-- > 1)
2324 {
2325 carry_out = ((*addr AND MSB) != 0);
2326 *addr <<= 1;
2327 if (carry_in) *addr |= LSB;
2328 carry_in = carry_out;
2329 addr++;
2330 }
2331 carry_out = ((*addr AND msb) != 0);
2332 *addr <<= 1;
2333 if (carry_in) *addr |= LSB;
2334 *addr &= mask;
2335 }
2336 return(carry_out);
2337}

2339boolean BitVector_rotate_right(wordptr addr)
2340{
2341 N_word size = size_(addr);
2342 N_word mask = mask_(addr);
2343 N_word msb;
2344 boolean carry_in;
2345 boolean carry_out = FALSE;
2346
2347 if (size > 0)
2348 {
2349 msb = mask AND NOT (mask >> 1);
2350 carry_in = ((*addr AND LSB) != 0);
2351 addr += size-1;
2352 *addr &= mask;
2353 carry_out = ((*addr AND LSB) != 0);
2354 *addr >>= 1;
2355 if (carry_in) *addr |= msb;
2356 carry_in = carry_out;
2357 addr--;
2358 size--;
2359 while (size-- > 0)
2360 {
2361 carry_out = ((*addr AND LSB) != 0);
2362 *addr >>= 1;
2363 if (carry_in) *addr |= MSB;
2364 carry_in = carry_out;
2365 addr--;
2366 }
2367 }
2368 return(carry_out);
2369}

2498{

2535
2536boolean BitVector_compute(wordptr X, wordptr Y, wordptr Z, boolean minus, boolean *carry)
2537{
2538 N_word size = size_(X);
2539 N_word mask = mask_(X);
2540 N_word vv = 0;
2541 N_word cc;
2542 N_word mm;
2543 N_word yy;
2544 N_word zz;
2545 N_word lo;
2546 N_word hi;
2547
2548 if (size > 0)
2549 {
2550 if (minus) cc = (*carry == 0);
2551 else cc = (*carry != 0);
2552 /* deal with (size-1) least significant full words first: */
2553 while (--size > 0)
2554 {
2555 yy = *Y++;
2556 if (minus) zz = (N_word) NOT ( Z ? *Z++ : 0 );
2557 else zz = (N_word) ( Z ? *Z++ : 0 );
2558 lo = (yy AND LSB) + (zz AND LSB) + cc;
2559 hi = (yy >> 1) + (zz >> 1) + (lo >> 1);
2560 cc = ((hi AND MSB) != 0);
2561 *X++ = (hi << 1) OR (lo AND LSB);
2562 }
2563 /* deal with most significant word (may be used only partially): */
2564 yy = *Y AND mask;
2565 if (minus) zz = (N_word) NOT ( Z ? *Z : 0 );
2566 else zz = (N_word) ( Z ? *Z : 0 );
2567 zz &= mask;
2568 if (mask == LSB) /* special case, only one bit used */
2569 {
2570 vv = cc;
2571 lo = yy + zz + cc;
2572 cc = (lo >> 1);
2573 vv ^= cc;
2574 *X = lo AND LSB;
2575 }
2576 else
2577 {
2578 if (NOT mask) /* not all bits are used, but more than one */
2579 {
2580 mm = (mask >> 1);
2581 vv = (yy AND mm) + (zz AND mm) + cc;
2582 mm = mask AND NOT mm;
2583 lo = yy + zz + cc;
2584 cc = (lo >> 1);
2585 vv ^= cc;
2586 vv &= mm;
2587 cc &= mm;
2588 *X = lo AND mask;
2589 }
2590 else /* other special case, all bits are used */
2591 {
2592 mm = NOT MSB;
2593 lo = (yy AND mm) + (zz AND mm) + cc;
2594 vv = lo AND MSB;
2595 hi = ((yy AND MSB) >> 1) + ((zz AND MSB) >> 1) + (vv >> 1);
2596 cc = hi AND MSB;
2597 vv ^= cc;
2598 *X = (hi << 1) OR (lo AND mm);
2599 }
2600 }
2601 if (minus) *carry = (cc == 0);
2602 else *carry = (cc != 0);
2603 }
2604 return(vv != 0);
2605}

2631void BitVector_Negate(wordptr X, wordptr Y)
2632{

2639 while (size-- > 0)
2640 {
2641 *X = NOT *Y++;
2642 if (carry)

2644 carry = (++(*X) == 0);
2645 }
2646 X++;

2649 }

2664Z_int BitVector_Sign(wordptr addr)
2665{

2667 N_word mask = mask_(addr);
2668 wordptr last = addr + size - 1;
2669 boolean r = TRUE;
2670

2672 {
2673 *last &= mask;
2674 while (r and (size-- > 0)) r = ( *addr++ == 0 );
2675 }
2676 if (r) return((Z_int) 0);

2684ErrCode BitVector_Mul_Pos(wordptr X, wordptr Y, wordptr Z, boolean strict)
2685{
2686 N_word mask;
2687 N_word limit;
2688 N_word count;
2689 Z_long last;
2690 wordptr sign;
2691 boolean carry;
2692 boolean overflow;
2693 boolean ok = TRUE;
2694
2695 /*
2696 Requirements:
2697 - X, Y and Z must be distinct
2698 - X and Y must have equal sizes (whereas Z may be any size!)
2699 - Z should always contain the SMALLER of the two factors Y and Z
2700 Constraints:
2701 - The contents of Y (and of X, of course) are destroyed
2702 (only Z is preserved!)
2703 */
2704
2705 if ((X == Y) or (X == Z) or (Y == Z)) return(ErrCode_Same);
2706 if (bits_(X) != bits_(Y)) return(ErrCode_Size);
2707 BitVector_Empty(X);
2708 if (BitVector_is_empty(Y)) return(ErrCode_Ok); /* exit also taken if bits_(Y)==0 */
2709 if ((last = Set_Max(Z)) < 0L) return(ErrCode_Ok);
2710 limit = (N_word) last;
2711 sign = Y + size_(Y) - 1;
2712 mask = mask_(Y);
2713 *sign &= mask;
2714 mask &= NOT (mask >> 1);
2715 for ( count = 0; (ok and (count <= limit)); count++ )
2716 {
2717 if ( BIT_VECTOR_TST_BIT(Z,count) )
2718 {
2719 carry = false;
2720 overflow = BitVector_compute(X,X,Y,false,&carry);
2721 if (strict) ok = not (carry or overflow);
2722 else ok = not carry;
2723 }
2724 if (ok and (count < limit))
2725 {
2726 carry = BitVector_shift_left(Y,0);
2727 if (strict)
2728 {
2729 overflow = ((*sign AND mask) != 0);
2730 ok = not (carry or overflow);
2731 }
2732 else ok = not carry;
2733 }
2734 }
2735 if (ok) return(ErrCode_Ok); else return(ErrCode_Ovfl);
2736}

2738ErrCode BitVector_Multiply(wordptr X, wordptr Y, wordptr Z)
2739{
2740 ErrCode error = ErrCode_Ok;
2741 N_word bit_x = bits_(X);
2742 N_word bit_y = bits_(Y);
2743 N_word bit_z = bits_(Z);
2744 N_word size;
2745 N_word mask;
2746 N_word msb;
2747 wordptr ptr_y;
2748 wordptr ptr_z;
2749 boolean sgn_x;
2750 boolean sgn_y;
2751 boolean sgn_z;
2752 boolean zero;
2753 wordptr A;
2754 wordptr B;
2755
2756 /*
2757 Requirements:
2758 - Y and Z must have equal sizes
2759 - X must have at least the same size as Y and Z but may be larger (!)
2760 Features:
2761 - The contents of Y and Z are preserved
2762 - X may be identical with Y or Z (or both!)
2763 (in-place multiplication is possible!)
2764 */
2765
2766 if ((bit_y != bit_z) or (bit_x < bit_y)) return(ErrCode_Size);
2767 if (BitVector_is_empty(Y) or BitVector_is_empty(Z))
2768 {
2769 BitVector_Empty(X);
2770 }
2771 else
2772 {
2773 A = BitVector_Create(bit_y,FALSE);
2774 if (A == NULL) return(ErrCode_Null);
2775 B = BitVector_Create(bit_z,FALSE);
2776 if (B == NULL) { BitVector_Destroy(A); return(ErrCode_Null); }
2777 size = size_(Y);
2778 mask = mask_(Y);
2779 msb = (mask AND NOT (mask >> 1));
2780 sgn_y = (((*(Y+size-1) &= mask) AND msb) != 0);
2781 sgn_z = (((*(Z+size-1) &= mask) AND msb) != 0);
2782 sgn_x = sgn_y XOR sgn_z;
2783 if (sgn_y) BitVector_Negate(A,Y); else BitVector_Copy(A,Y);
2784 if (sgn_z) BitVector_Negate(B,Z); else BitVector_Copy(B,Z);
2785 ptr_y = A + size;
2786 ptr_z = B + size;
2787 zero = TRUE;
2788 while (zero and (size-- > 0))
2789 {
2790 zero &= (*(--ptr_y) == 0);
2791 zero &= (*(--ptr_z) == 0);
2792 }
2793 if (*ptr_y > *ptr_z)
2794 {
2795 if (bit_x > bit_y)
2796 {
2797 A = BitVector_Resize(A,bit_x);
2798 if (A == NULL) { BitVector_Destroy(B); return(ErrCode_Null); }
2799 }
2800 error = BitVector_Mul_Pos(X,A,B,TRUE);
2801 }
2802 else
2803 {
2804 if (bit_x > bit_z)
2805 {
2806 B = BitVector_Resize(B,bit_x);
2807 if (B == NULL) { BitVector_Destroy(A); return(ErrCode_Null); }
2808 }
2809 error = BitVector_Mul_Pos(X,B,A,TRUE);
2810 }
2811 if ((not error) and sgn_x) BitVector_Negate(X,X);
2812 BitVector_Destroy(A);
2813 BitVector_Destroy(B);
2814 }
2815 return(error);
2816}
2817
2818ErrCode BitVector_Div_Pos(wordptr Q, wordptr X, wordptr Y, wordptr R)
2819{
2820 N_word bits = bits_(Q);
2821 N_word mask;
2822 wordptr addr;
2823 Z_long last;
2824 boolean flag;
2825 boolean copy = FALSE; /* flags whether valid rest is in R (0) or X (1) */
2826
2827 /*
2828 Requirements:
2829 - All bit vectors must have equal sizes
2830 - Q, X, Y and R must all be distinct bit vectors
2831 - Y must be non-zero (of course!)
2832 Constraints:
2833 - The contents of X (and Q and R, of course) are destroyed
2834 (only Y is preserved!)
2835 */
2836
2837 if ((bits != bits_(X)) or (bits != bits_(Y)) or (bits != bits_(R)))
2838 return(ErrCode_Size);
2839 if ((Q == X) or (Q == Y) or (Q == R) or (X == Y) or (X == R) or (Y == R))
2840 return(ErrCode_Same);
2841 if (BitVector_is_empty(Y))
2842 return(ErrCode_Zero);
2843
2844 BitVector_Empty(R);
2845 BitVector_Copy(Q,X);
2846 if ((last = Set_Max(Q)) < 0L) return(ErrCode_Ok);
2847 bits = (N_word) ++last;
2848 while (bits-- > 0)
2849 {
2850 addr = Q + (bits >> LOGBITS);
2851 mask = BITMASKTAB[bits AND MODMASK];
2852 flag = ((*addr AND mask) != 0);
2853 if (copy)
2854 {
2855 BitVector_shift_left(X,flag);
2856 flag = FALSE;
2857 BitVector_compute(R,X,Y,TRUE,&flag);
2858 }
2859 else
2860 {
2861 BitVector_shift_left(R,flag);
2862 flag = FALSE;
2863 BitVector_compute(X,R,Y,TRUE,&flag);
2864 }
2865 if (flag) *addr &= NOT mask;
2866 else
2867 {
2868 *addr |= mask;
2869 copy = not copy;
2870 }
2871 }
2872 if (copy) BitVector_Copy(R,X);
2873 return(ErrCode_Ok);
2874}
2875
2876ErrCode BitVector_Divide(wordptr Q, wordptr X, wordptr Y, wordptr R)
2877{
2878 ErrCode error = ErrCode_Ok;
2879 N_word bits = bits_(Q);
2880 N_word size = size_(Q);
2881 N_word mask = mask_(Q);
2882 N_word msb = (mask AND NOT (mask >> 1));
2883 boolean sgn_q;
2884 boolean sgn_x;
2885 boolean sgn_y;
2886 wordptr A;
2887 wordptr B;
2888
2889 /*
2890 Requirements:
2891 - All bit vectors must have equal sizes
2892 - Q and R must be two distinct bit vectors
2893 - Y must be non-zero (of course!)
2894 Features:
2895 - The contents of X and Y are preserved
2896 - Q may be identical with X or Y (or both)
2897 (in-place division is possible!)
2898 - R may be identical with X or Y (or both)
2899 (but not identical with Q!)
2900 */
2901
2902 if ((bits != bits_(X)) or (bits != bits_(Y)) or (bits != bits_(R)))
2903 return(ErrCode_Size);
2904 if (Q == R)
2905 return(ErrCode_Same);
2906 if (BitVector_is_empty(Y))
2907 return(ErrCode_Zero);
2908
2909 if (BitVector_is_empty(X))
2910 {
2911 BitVector_Empty(Q);
2912 BitVector_Empty(R);
2913 }
2914 else
2915 {
2916 A = BitVector_Create(bits,FALSE);
2917 if (A == NULL) return(ErrCode_Null);
2918 B = BitVector_Create(bits,FALSE);
2919 if (B == NULL) { BitVector_Destroy(A); return(ErrCode_Null); }
2920 size--;
2921 sgn_x = (((*(X+size) &= mask) AND msb) != 0);
2922 sgn_y = (((*(Y+size) &= mask) AND msb) != 0);
2923 sgn_q = sgn_x XOR sgn_y;
2924 if (sgn_x) BitVector_Negate(A,X); else BitVector_Copy(A,X);
2925 if (sgn_y) BitVector_Negate(B,Y); else BitVector_Copy(B,Y);
2926 if (not (error = BitVector_Div_Pos(Q,A,B,R)))
2927 {
2928 if (sgn_q) BitVector_Negate(Q,Q);
2929 if (sgn_x) BitVector_Negate(R,R);
2930 }
2931 BitVector_Destroy(A);
2932 BitVector_Destroy(B);
2933 }
2934 return(error);
2935}

2937ErrCode BitVector_GCD(wordptr X, wordptr Y, wordptr Z)
2938{
2939 ErrCode error = ErrCode_Ok;
2940 N_word bits = bits_(X);
2941 N_word size = size_(X);
2942 N_word mask = mask_(X);
2943 N_word msb = (mask AND NOT (mask >> 1));
2944 boolean sgn_a;
2945 boolean sgn_b;
2946 boolean sgn_r;
2947 wordptr Q;
2948 wordptr R;
2949 wordptr A;
2950 wordptr B;
2951 wordptr T;
2952
2953 /*
2954 Requirements:
2955 - All bit vectors must have equal sizes
2956 Features:
2957 - The contents of Y and Z are preserved
2958 - X may be identical with Y or Z (or both)
2959 (in-place is possible!)
2960 - GCD(0,z) == GCD(z,0) == z
2961 - negative values are handled correctly
2962 */
2963
2964 if ((bits != bits_(Y)) or (bits != bits_(Z))) return(ErrCode_Size);
2965 if (BitVector_is_empty(Y))
2966 {
2967 if (X != Z) BitVector_Copy(X,Z);
2968 return(ErrCode_Ok);
2969 }
2970 if (BitVector_is_empty(Z))
2971 {
2972 if (X != Y) BitVector_Copy(X,Y);
2973 return(ErrCode_Ok);
2974 }
2975 Q = BitVector_Create(bits,false);
2976 if (Q == NULL)
2977 {
2978 return(ErrCode_Null);
2979 }
2980 R = BitVector_Create(bits,FALSE);
2981 if (R == NULL)
2982 {
2983 BitVector_Destroy(Q);
2984 return(ErrCode_Null);
2985 }
2986 A = BitVector_Create(bits,FALSE);
2987 if (A == NULL)
2988 {
2989 BitVector_Destroy(Q);
2990 BitVector_Destroy(R);
2991 return(ErrCode_Null);
2992 }
2993 B = BitVector_Create(bits,FALSE);
2994 if (B == NULL)
2995 {
2996 BitVector_Destroy(Q);
2997 BitVector_Destroy(R);
2998 BitVector_Destroy(A);
2999 return(ErrCode_Null);
3000 }
3001 size--;
3002 sgn_a = (((*(Y+size) &= mask) AND msb) != 0);
3003 sgn_b = (((*(Z+size) &= mask) AND msb) != 0);
3004 if (sgn_a) BitVector_Negate(A,Y); else BitVector_Copy(A,Y);
3005 if (sgn_b) BitVector_Negate(B,Z); else BitVector_Copy(B,Z);
3006 while (not error)
3007 {
3008 if (not (error = BitVector_Div_Pos(Q,A,B,R)))
3009 {
3010 if (BitVector_is_empty(R)) break;
3011 T = A; sgn_r = sgn_a;
3012 A = B; sgn_a = sgn_b;
3013 B = R; sgn_b = sgn_r;
3014 R = T;
3015 }
3016 }
3017 if (not error)
3018 {
3019 if (sgn_b) BitVector_Negate(X,B); else BitVector_Copy(X,B);
3020 }
3021 BitVector_Destroy(Q);
3022 BitVector_Destroy(R);
3023 BitVector_Destroy(A);
3024 BitVector_Destroy(B);
3025 return(error);
3026}

3028ErrCode BitVector_GCD2(wordptr U, wordptr V, wordptr W, wordptr X, wordptr Y)
3029{
3030 ErrCode error = ErrCode_Ok;
3031 N_word bits = bits_(U);
3032 N_word size = size_(U);
3033 N_word mask = mask_(U);
3034 N_word msb = (mask AND NOT (mask >> 1));
3035 boolean minus;
3036 boolean carry;
3037 boolean sgn_q;
3038 boolean sgn_r;
3039 boolean sgn_a;
3040 boolean sgn_b;
3041 boolean sgn_x;
3042 boolean sgn_y;
3043 listptr L;
3044 wordptr Q;
3045 wordptr R;
3046 wordptr A;
3047 wordptr B;
3048 wordptr T;
3049 wordptr X1;
3050 wordptr X2;
3051 wordptr X3;
3052 wordptr Y1;
3053 wordptr Y2;
3054 wordptr Y3;
3055 wordptr Z;
3056
3057 /*
3058 Requirements:
3059 - All bit vectors must have equal sizes
3060 - U, V, and W must all be distinct bit vectors
3061 Features:
3062 - The contents of X and Y are preserved
3063 - U, V and W may be identical with X or Y (or both,
3064 provided that U, V and W are mutually distinct)
3065 (i.e., in-place is possible!)
3066 - GCD(0,z) == GCD(z,0) == z
3067 - negative values are handled correctly
3068 */
3069
3070 if ((bits != bits_(V)) or
3071 (bits != bits_(W)) or
3072 (bits != bits_(X)) or
3073 (bits != bits_(Y)))
3074 {
3075 return(ErrCode_Size);
3076 }
3077 if ((U == V) or (U == W) or (V == W))
3078 {
3079 return(ErrCode_Same);
3080 }
3081 if (BitVector_is_empty(X))
3082 {
3083 if (U != Y) BitVector_Copy(U,Y);
3084 BitVector_Empty(V);
3085 BitVector_Empty(W);
3086 *W = 1;
3087 return(ErrCode_Ok);
3088 }
3089 if (BitVector_is_empty(Y))
3090 {
3091 if (U != X) BitVector_Copy(U,X);
3092 BitVector_Empty(V);
3093 BitVector_Empty(W);
3094 *V = 1;
3095 return(ErrCode_Ok);
3096 }
3097 if ((L = BitVector_Create_List(bits,false,11)) == NULL)
3098 {
3099 return(ErrCode_Null);
3100 }
3101 Q = L[0];
3102 R = L[1];
3103 A = L[2];
3104 B = L[3];
3105 X1 = L[4];
3106 X2 = L[5];
3107 X3 = L[6];
3108 Y1 = L[7];
3109 Y2 = L[8];
3110 Y3 = L[9];
3111 Z = L[10];
3112 size--;
3113 sgn_a = (((*(X+size) &= mask) AND msb) != 0);
3114 sgn_b = (((*(Y+size) &= mask) AND msb) != 0);
3115 if (sgn_a) BitVector_Negate(A,X); else BitVector_Copy(A,X);
3116 if (sgn_b) BitVector_Negate(B,Y); else BitVector_Copy(B,Y);
3117 BitVector_Empty(X1);
3118 BitVector_Empty(X2);
3119 *X1 = 1;
3120 BitVector_Empty(Y1);
3121 BitVector_Empty(Y2);
3122 *Y2 = 1;
3123 sgn_x = false;
3124 sgn_y = false;
3125 while (not error)
3126 {
3127 if ((error = BitVector_Div_Pos(Q,A,B,R)))
3128 {
3129 break;
3130 }
3131 if (BitVector_is_empty(R))
3132 {
3133 break;
3134 }
3135 sgn_q = sgn_a XOR sgn_b;
3136
3137 if (sgn_x) BitVector_Negate(Z,X2); else BitVector_Copy(Z,X2);
3138 if ((error = BitVector_Mul_Pos(X3,Z,Q,true)))
3139 {
3140 break;
3141 }
3142 minus = not (sgn_x XOR sgn_q);
3143 carry = 0;
3144 if (BitVector_compute(X3,X1,X3,minus,&carry))
3145 {
3146 error = ErrCode_Ovfl;
3147 break;
3148 }
3149 sgn_x = (((*(X3+size) &= mask) AND msb) != 0);
3150
3151 if (sgn_y) BitVector_Negate(Z,Y2); else BitVector_Copy(Z,Y2);
3152 if ((error = BitVector_Mul_Pos(Y3,Z,Q,true)))
3153 {
3154 break;
3155 }
3156 minus = not (sgn_y XOR sgn_q);
3157 carry = 0;
3158 if (BitVector_compute(Y3,Y1,Y3,minus,&carry))
3159 {
3160 error = ErrCode_Ovfl;
3161 break;
3162 }
3163 sgn_y = (((*(Y3+size) &= mask) AND msb) != 0);
3164
3165 T = A; sgn_r = sgn_a;
3166 A = B; sgn_a = sgn_b;
3167 B = R; sgn_b = sgn_r;
3168 R = T;
3169
3170 T = X1;
3171 X1 = X2;
3172 X2 = X3;
3173 X3 = T;
3174
3175 T = Y1;
3176 Y1 = Y2;
3177 Y2 = Y3;
3178 Y3 = T;
3179 }
3180 if (not error)
3181 {
3182 if (sgn_b) BitVector_Negate(U,B); else BitVector_Copy(U,B);
3183 BitVector_Copy(V,X2);
3184 BitVector_Copy(W,Y2);
3185 }
3186 BitVector_Destroy_List(L,11);
3187 return(error);
3188}

3190ErrCode BitVector_Power(wordptr X, wordptr Y, wordptr Z)
3191{
3192 ErrCode error = ErrCode_Ok;
3193 N_word bits = bits_(X);
3194 boolean first = TRUE;
3195 Z_long last;
3196 N_word limit;
3197 N_word count;
3198 wordptr T;
3199
3200 /*
3201 Requirements:
3202 - X must have at least the same size as Y but may be larger (!)
3203 - X may not be identical with Z
3204 - Z must be positive
3205 Features:
3206 - The contents of Y and Z are preserved
3207 */
3208
3209 if (X == Z) return(ErrCode_Same);
3210 if (bits < bits_(Y)) return(ErrCode_Size);
3211 if (BitVector_msb_(Z)) return(ErrCode_Expo);
3212 if ((last = Set_Max(Z)) < 0L)
3213 {
3214 if (bits < 2) return(ErrCode_Ovfl);
3215 BitVector_Empty(X);
3216 *X |= LSB;
3217 return(ErrCode_Ok); /* anything ^ 0 == 1 */
3218 }
3219 if (BitVector_is_empty(Y))
3220 {
3221 if (X != Y) BitVector_Empty(X);
3222 return(ErrCode_Ok); /* 0 ^ anything not zero == 0 */
3223 }
3224 T = BitVector_Create(bits,FALSE);
3225 if (T == NULL) return(ErrCode_Null);
3226 limit = (N_word) last;
3227 for ( count = 0; ((!error) and (count <= limit)); count++ )
3228 {
3229 if ( BIT_VECTOR_TST_BIT(Z,count) )
3230 {
3231 if (first)
3232 {
3233 first = FALSE;
3234 if (count) { BitVector_Copy(X,T); }
3235 else { if (X != Y) BitVector_Copy(X,Y); }
3236 }
3237 else error = BitVector_Multiply(X,T,X); /* order important because T > X */
3238 }
3239 if ((!error) and (count < limit))
3240 {
3241 if (count) error = BitVector_Multiply(T,T,T);
3242 else error = BitVector_Multiply(T,Y,Y);
3243 }
3244 }
3245 BitVector_Destroy(T);
3246 return(error);
3247}

3358void BitVector_Chunk_Store(wordptr addr, N_int chunksize, N_int offset,
3359 N_long value)
3360{
3361 N_word bits = bits_(addr);
3362 N_word mask;
3363 N_word temp;
3364
3365 if ((chunksize > 0) and (offset < bits))
3366 {
3367 if (chunksize > LONGBITS) chunksize = LONGBITS;
3368 if ((offset + chunksize) > bits) chunksize = bits - offset;
3369 addr += offset >> LOGBITS;
3370 offset &= MODMASK;
3371 while (chunksize > 0)
3372 {
3373 mask = (N_word) (~0L << offset);
3374 bits = offset + chunksize;
3375 if (bits < BITS)
3376 {
3377 mask &= (N_word) ~(~0L << bits);
3378 bits = chunksize;
3379 }
3380 else bits = BITS - offset;
3381 temp = (N_word) (value << offset);
3382 temp &= mask;
3383 *addr &= NOT mask;
3384 *addr++ |= temp;
3385 value >>= bits;
3386 chunksize -= bits;
3387 offset = 0;
3388 }
3389 }
3390}
3391
3392N_long BitVector_Chunk_Read(wordptr addr, N_int chunksize, N_int offset)
3393{
3394 N_word bits = bits_(addr);
3395 N_word chunkbits = 0;
3396 N_long value = 0L;
3397 N_long temp;
3398 N_word mask;
3399
3400 if ((chunksize > 0) and (offset < bits))
3401 {
3402 if (chunksize > LONGBITS) chunksize = LONGBITS;
3403 if ((offset + chunksize) > bits) chunksize = bits - offset;
3404 addr += offset >> LOGBITS;
3405 offset &= MODMASK;
3406 while (chunksize > 0)
3407 {
3408 bits = offset + chunksize;
3409 if (bits < BITS)
3410 {
3411 mask = (N_word) ~(~0L << bits);
3412 bits = chunksize;
3413 }
3414 else
3415 {
3416 mask = (N_word) ~0L;
3417 bits = BITS - offset;
3418 }
3419 temp = (N_long) ((*addr++ AND mask) >> offset);
3420 value |= temp << chunkbits;
3421 chunkbits += bits;
3422 chunksize -= bits;
3423 offset = 0;
3424 }
3425 }
3426 return(value);

3739void Matrix_Transpose(wordptr X, N_int rowsX, N_int colsX,
3740 wordptr Y, N_int rowsY, N_int colsY)
3741{
3742 N_word i;
3743 N_word j;
3744 N_word ii;
3745 N_word ij;
3746 N_word ji;
3747 N_word addii;
3748 N_word addij;
3749 N_word addji;
3750 N_word bitii;
3751 N_word bitij;
3752 N_word bitji;
3753 N_word termi;
3754 N_word termj;
3755 boolean swap;
3756
3757 /* BEWARE that "in-place" is ONLY possible if the matrix is quadratic!! */
3758
3759 if ((rowsX == colsY) and (colsX == rowsY) and
3760 (bits_(X) == rowsX*colsX) and
3761 (bits_(Y) == rowsY*colsY))
3762 {
3763 if (rowsY == colsY) /* in-place is possible! */
3764 {
3765 for ( i = 0; i < rowsY; i++ )
3766 {
3767 termi = i * colsY;
3768 for ( j = 0; j < i; j++ )
3769 {
3770 termj = j * colsX;
3771 ij = termi + j;
3772 ji = termj + i;
3773 addij = ij >> LOGBITS;
3774 addji = ji >> LOGBITS;
3775 bitij = BITMASKTAB[ij AND MODMASK];
3776 bitji = BITMASKTAB[ji AND MODMASK];
3777 swap = ((*(Y+addij) AND bitij) != 0);
3778 if ((*(Y+addji) AND bitji) != 0)
3779 *(X+addij) |= bitij;
3780 else
3781 *(X+addij) &= NOT bitij;
3782 if (swap)
3783 *(X+addji) |= bitji;
3784 else
3785 *(X+addji) &= NOT bitji;
3786 }
3787 ii = termi + i;
3788 addii = ii >> LOGBITS;
3789 bitii = BITMASKTAB[ii AND MODMASK];
3790 if ((*(Y+addii) AND bitii) != 0)
3791 *(X+addii) |= bitii;
3792 else
3793 *(X+addii) &= NOT bitii;
3794 }
3795 }
3796 else /* rowsX != colsX, in-place is NOT possible! */
3797 {
3798 for ( i = 0; i < rowsY; i++ )
3799 {
3800 termi = i * colsY;
3801 for ( j = 0; j < colsY; j++ )
3802 {
3803 termj = j * colsX;
3804 ij = termi + j;
3805 ji = termj + i;
3806 addij = ij >> LOGBITS;
3807 addji = ji >> LOGBITS;
3808 bitij = BITMASKTAB[ij AND MODMASK];
3809 bitji = BITMASKTAB[ji AND MODMASK];
3810 if ((*(Y+addij) AND bitij) != 0)
3811 *(X+addji) |= bitji;
3812 else
3813 *(X+addji) &= NOT bitji;
3814 }
3815 }
3816 }
3817 }
3818}
